# GAIA COM COIN – LICENSE PROTOCOL

Version 1.0
Copyright © VisionGaiaTechnology

---

## 1. Overview

This repository uses a **multi-license structure** to balance:

* Open-source collaboration
* Security, auditability, and trust
* Protection of governance, tokenomics, and ethical foundations

Different parts of the codebase are licensed under different licenses, as described below.

This approach is intentional and aligned with best practices for critical protocol infrastructure.

---

## 2. License Matrix

| Component                      | Path          | License                     |
| ------------------------------ | ------------- | --------------------------- |
| Core protocol logic            | `/core`       | Apache License 2.0          |
| Cryptography                   | `/crypto`     | Apache License 2.0          |
| Networking (P2P)               | `/net`        | Apache License 2.0          |
| Consensus engine               | `/consensus`  | Apache License 2.0          |
| Governance & voting logic      | `/governance` | Business Source License 1.1 |
| Tokenomics & monetary policy   | `/tokenomics` | Business Source License 1.1 |
| Documentation & specifications | `/docs`       | Creative Commons BY-SA 4.0  |
| Scripts & tooling              | `/scripts`    | MIT License                 |

Each directory contains its own `LICENSE` file with the applicable terms.

---

## 3. Apache License 2.0

### (Core Protocol, Crypto, Networking, Consensus)

The following components are licensed under the **Apache License, Version 2.0**:

* Core protocol implementation
* Cryptographic primitives and integrations
* Peer-to-peer networking stack
* Consensus and validation logic

The Apache License 2.0 grants:

* Free use, modification, and distribution
* Commercial use
* Explicit patent grant and protection

Full license text:
[https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0](https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0)

